parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Steer Tire Wear and Front End Vibration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear on steer tires can lead to loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and accidents. Front end vibration can cause driver fatigue, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
Frame and suspension issues can cause loss of vehicle control, premature wear on components, and accidents.
Steering system issues can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sleeper Wall Side Seams Water Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leakage through the sleeper wall side seams can cause damage to the interior, electrical systems, and cargo, leading to safety hazards, corrosion, and costly repairs.
symptoms: Water leaks into the sleeper compartment
water spots or stains on the walls or ceiling
rust or corrosion on metal components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake vibration can cause loss of control, increased stopping distance, and reduced braking performance, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Vibration felt in the steering wheel
or floor when applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Jumping Out of Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or jumping out of gear can cause loss of vehicle control, especially when driving on hills or under load, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or jumps out of gear
the vehicle loses power or speed
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the vehicle hesitates or stutters when shifting gears.
